For deploying my applications, I have a simple deployment pipeline that uses AWS Serverless Application Model (SAM), GitHub, and Circle CI. If you're not familiar with CI/CD, here's [a post that introduces it well](https://semaphoreci.com/blog/cicd-pipeline).

Many people (myself included) get started with Lambda by writing functions directly in the console. Getting a CI/CD pipeline set up and getting comfortable with it made *such* a difference in my development experience. It can be painful to go through all the set up for the first time, but it will become second nature once you've set up a project or two and experienced how magical it is when it's working smoothly!

